@mengxr Thanks for your review! I've addressed all suggestions, except: 1)I used Experimental annotation for the whole class only. Do I need to annotate each method? 2)I removed the prefix "micro" from 3 methods, but I didn't remove recall and fMeasure. I think it might be confusing that there is precision and no recall and fMeasure methods despite their equality. 

I think handling the models with raw score should be done in a separate class, that knows the model output. Some models output the number between 0 and 1 (Bayesian), some output either 0 either 1 (Logistic Regression), the other -1 or 1 (SVM). Ultimately, I would like that all models return class or no_class by default and the raw score optionally. What do you think?

Could you review my pull request for multilabel measures? https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/1270
